Restaurant
Our restaurant is open to our
members and their guests
seven days a week.
Club members enjoy fine dining, in our casually elegant and intimate setting, as well as casual affairs such as Tavern Night, BBQ cookouts, and member mixers. Prix-Fixe Nights and our Sunday brunches are additional popular dining events. Our dining room, complete with full bar service, has a large dance floor and an expansive view of the beautifully landscaped golf course. The dining room is open daily for lunch from 9 am to 3 pm. Fine Dining is every Friday and Saturday from 5:30 pm to 8:00 pm, these are non-season hours, but during the season the availability for fine dining increases.
End Mini-Page 20041

3.4.1
Our Club
History
Begin Mini-Page 20101
The Key Royale Club is a
members only
private club.
The "GEM of AMI" is a truly unique club with an "old-Florida" feel.
Our mission is to provide our members and their guests with the “Key Royale Experience”, a private equity club with a friendly island vibe combined with outstanding golf, amenities, food and service.
End Mini-Page 20101
Begin Mini-Page 20102
The Key Royale Club was organized on April 2, 1965, with 96 founding members. The course opened for play on September 24, 1966, and the club house opened December 31, 1966.
The golf course was created to market a new housing development of 125 acres on what was School Key. School Key, a 150 acre island just off the north eastern side of Anna Maria Island, was mangrove swamps and jungles when it was purchased by developer Peder Mickelsen.
Mickelsen, who resided in Minnesota and wintered on Anna Maria Island, cleared the jungles and planned home sites with the goal of every lot having access to open waters. The Army Corps of Engineers excavated the canals and thus began the Key Royale neighborhood.
William Lee, a home builder also from Minnesota, built a home on Key Royale Drive and became the primary builder for the development. Howard Adams, a local real estate agent, was the primary real estate sale agent. As friends and neighbors, Mickelsen and these men decided that building a golf course would help market the project. It was decided that the course would be built on 29 acres that were not conducive to being dredged.
These three men and Arthur Reppenhagen, Sr., pledged $25,000, thus becoming the original financial investors for the club. Howard Adams became the first president of the new club in 1965 and Arthur Reppenhagen, Sr. was the author of the club’s original bylaws.
End Mini-Page 20102
End Tabs

Membership Information
The Key Royale Club is a member-owned private Club on Anna
Maria Island, Florida offering golf and social memberships.
The Key Royale Club’s membership and waitlist for golf and
social is currently at full capacity.
If you would like to leave your contact information in the
event the waitlist re-opens, please fill out the form at the bottom of this
page.
Thank you for your interest in the Key Royale Club.
* Golfing Member is an individual or couple whose application has been given final approval by the Board of Directors, who has purchased a single share of stock and paid all the required fees established by the Board of Directors. The number of Regular Golfing Members is limited by the Board of Directors. If a two- person household, the significant other must maintain a Social Member membership status, at a minimum.
* Social Members may use the Club House, but to use the golf course, must comply with guest rules and pay applicable fees. Social Members may participate in limited Club non-sanctioned golfing events and have limited guest privileges.
End Mini-Page 20029
